Welcome to the Apico two-stroke festival video editing competition. We want to find the most talented video editors out there and are offering a £200 prize to the winner. 

Do you have the creativity and the technical expertise it takes to win? Here’s what you need to do: if you’re interested or know someone that could be, comment or tag them in the comments and we will message you or them directly with our two-stroke festival footage. 

Once you have the footage, it’s time to start editing. Put together your masterpiece and send it back to us. We will then review all of the entries and select a winner based on creativity and technical skill. Everyone will have the same footage to create a edit with, which will be around 5/10 minutes long ( Old festival 🎦) 

To make sure your video stands out from the crowd, we suggest exploring different styles and techniques. You could start by cutting between angles or adding different effects or transitions for a polished, professional look. You could also experiment with colour grading or audio to give your video that cutting edge. 

The competition closes on the end of February and we will announce the winner soon after. So if you think you have what it takes, don’t delay – Good luck and we look forward to seeing your work.

Ps If we get a number of good standard videos - we post them out on our our 2-stroke festival socials to see what the public like 👍🏻 Pc @motoheadmag

Hey dirt bike fans – welcome to the world of @arenacrossuk 

This highly competitive off-road racing that is enjoyed by both professionals and amateurs in the UK is awesome atm. 

At its core, AX is an adrenaline-filled sport that pushes riders to their physical and mental limit. It requires skill, strength, and strategy to achieve the WIN and just compete. But that’s not all – it also requires a great deal of dedication and passion to truly excel in the sport.

OFF road motorsport is a culture – a tight-knit community of riders and enthusiasts who share a common bond. There’s a mutual respect that’s earned through hard work and dedication, and each rider can learn from one another. These experiences bring people from all walks of life together, building lifelong friendships - FACT. It’s also a brilliant way of teaching life skills!

Beyond the culture, motocross has a thriving social media presence, with dedicated Instagram, Twitter, and YouTube personalities engaging in the sport and its related activities. Atm I’m proud to be British and to see our SPORT being promoted to the highest level #PositiveVibes ✊🏻 If you haven’t watched by a ticket and if you can’t buy a ticket - watch it for free on YouTube 👍🏻

2007 was an amazing year for me. I had the opportunity to live out my dream of racing nearly every weekend and had some of the best riders. But it wasn’t just about the racing: 2007 was also the year that I got married. 

At the end of October, I married the love of my life and in the following June we welcomed our first baby boy into the world. Racing motocross had already been an intense adrenaline rush but it was nothing compared to the joy and excitement of becoming a parent. 

It was a unforgettable year and one that will always remain close to my heart. I learned a lot about myself and motocross, but most importantly, I learned the true value of friendship, family and most importantly, love. Ps @kellywillet I’ll be away again this weekend but #ItsNotAHoliday 😘

Good evening everyone! I am pleased to announce the date for the festival we’ve been running over the past few years.

It’s always tough to choose a date as I want to make sure it doesn’t clash with other events and gives everyone time to prepare and join in. But this is getting harder and harder to achieve. 

I started this event with a focus on 2- strokes only but have since added more options as the event has continued in order to make the event bigger, better, and more enjoyable for everyone involved. We wanted to give the PRO riders another platform to showcase themselves and be rewarded, while looking after the grass roots and the next generation of our sport. This year we could incorporate more again.! 

Over the years, I think it’s been clear that myself and everyone involved in this event have worked hard to create something that’s truly inspiring and fun - this will continue ✊🏻🎶

So make sure to mark your calendars and join us on  22/23 July for a weekend of FUN. I can’t wait to see you all there again and make it a day to remember.

Team GB Junior Worlds at Fatcat Moto Parc. This is the first event of its kind, and it is an opportunity for everyone to come together, have fun, and start building a strong and supportive community.

Team GB Junior Worlds update… 

Glen Phillips is one of Britain’s top motocross racers, Glen has earned a remarkable collection of accolades, including numerous ACU and BSMA British Championships ( 60/80/100/125 ), a Champion of Champions title, a British U21 winner, and 4-stroke victory. He’s achieved points in all GP classes, podiumed at the British Championships, MX1 and MX2 and has ranked in the Top 3 of British Supercross. He has also secured 2nd place in the FutureWest Supercross Championship and joined the U21 Coupe team at the young age of 14!

The proud Welshman Glen is now bringing his expertise and enthusiasm to Team GB Junior Worlds and is also helping with training at Fatcat. With his successes and experience, he’s sure to be an invaluable asset and mentor to all the new motocross racers.

Team GB junior worlds are looking forward to having @tommysearle100 at Fatcat Moto Parc today to share his experience and expertise with you! Don't miss out on the chance to benefit from his commitment to promoting motocross in the UK and his enthusiasm. He'll also be vlogging the day 

Tommy Searle is a three-time MX2 World Vice-Champion and four-time British Champion, British Arenacross champion making him one of the most successful riders in British motocross.  He will be returning to Fatcat Moto Parc to support Team GB, bringing his experience and knowledge to the team. 

Searle began his motocross career in 2005, competing in the Motocross World Championships for four years. After leaving the championship for two years, he returned in 2011 and stayed until 2019, when he achieved his greatest success - becoming the three-time MX2 World Vice-Champion. Showcasing his skills, he also has 14 MX2 Grand Prix victories to his name, making him the most successful MX2 rider in the UK.

Searle has a wealth of experience and a passion for the sport. His time in the championships has provided him with the skills to support Team GB as they strive towards success. His knowledge and enthusiasm will be a valuable asset on the team’s journey, as they look to reach new heights.

We’d like to extend a huge thank you to everyone who made the first Team GB JWC day a memorable one. Your presence and enthusiasm were truly appreciated, and it’s heartwarming to see the momentum building. We are confident that Team GB will go far. Unfortunately, the day ended a little sooner due to an unfortunate accident. Thankfully, the rider is doing well and recovering fast. We can’t wait to see him back on the track.

It was awesome to see everyone give it their all on track today. I’ve been getting a lot of questions about when the next track day will be, so once we finish our team debrief I’ll let everyone know - keep your eyes peeled!

Thank you all once again for making it a special day and supporting the cause 🇬🇧 @teamgbjwc_official

It has been a testing yet rewarding 48 hours for me, my family and friends – I have spent 15 of those hours driving in my van back and forth to Fatcats Moto Parc and attending meetings for the Team GB Junior World & Coupe event. Believe me I know it’s been no different from everyone involved too so I’m not looking for praise. #JustSaying 

I’m a luckily man to have such a understanding family and great team - it’s never easy to push your own family to the side to make sure things are put in place so huge shoutout to all the wife’s and partners which have made some sacrifices lately. 

Why we have pushed on is because the ACU and parents of these kids have put a lot of faith and trust in us, and we wanted to make sure to do right by them. Their investment into their children, without question, encourages me personally to keep pushing forward and I know everyone involved feels the same. Anyway, all of the hard work and long hours I feel was rewarded with positive energy at Fatcats everyone involved has motivated me even more BTW.

FYI the setup at the worlds and coupe is taking shape & believe me it’s going to 🤌🏻👌🏻. Also in the next 48 hours we hopefully will have secured another date and venue for Team GB junior worlds training. Thanks all for your support and input 🇬🇧

The Apico 2-Stroke Festival Featuring Red Bull Pro Stroke National event has become a huge hit in the UK with riders and fans, with its growing popularity and success providing a weekend for grass roots to high-end competitive its an event which has a cool unique atmosphere for all..

My wrap-up of the first Junior Worlds! 

First of all, I’d like to thank all of the riders and their parents, our sponsors, and each and every member of the team for their hard work and dedication. This weekend was an incredible and inspiring experience for us all. 

We’ve seen such a great level of enthusiasm, heart, and commitment from everyone this weekend, and it’s really been an absolute pleasure. 

It was a challenging yet rewarding experience. The riders worked tirelessly to stay focused and the efforts put in by each person was really inspiring to see. The potential within all of these young individuals is truly remarkable. 

The dedication and commitment that these riders have each demonstrated has been remarkable. They were always determined to put their best foot forward and really put their all into this event. 

I’m sure that the riders will take what they’ve learned this weekend and apply it to future events. 

It’s been an unforgettable experience that we’ll all cherish for a long time. Thank you all 🇬🇧

The Junior World Championships. It was an incredible experience and what a incredible venue. We went into it with a young team that had a lot of potential. 

To be honest, I honestly didn’t know what to expect leading up to the event. However, I couldn’t have been more proud of our team as 11 out of 13 of them actually qualified surprising themselves. This is an amazing achievement for us and a testament to everyone’s hard work and dedication. 

But what has really stood out to me was the effort that our boys gave in the last chance races. I honestly have not seen two better races in a long time - they really showed their heart and determination in those races. 

Going forward, this experience has taught me a lot - what needs to be done, how to best prepare the team, and I’m excited to put this into practice in the years to come. We have huge potential in the UK, I’m confident that we can do even better in the future 🇬🇧 

@mxjunior2023 @tcsracingpark 👍🏻
22/23 July be there 🇬🇧💪🏻

Monumental day, which will never be forgotten. Many deserve to have been up on stage to experience the feelings and emotions, but unfortunately, only a few are lucky enough to have that opportunity. 

Though we can’t sense it in this image, for those who were present, the air was filled with the smells of sweat and determination. This day didn’t come easy, by any means. Behind the scenes, there were hours of hard work, dedication, and many volunteer hours to make this moment possible. 

From unloading bikes and equipment, to doing practice starts and track walks, there were many factors that went into the lead up to the ceremony. For those who worked tirelessly behind the scenes, it was a sacrifice of time and effort without expecting anything in return, or even the luxury of being able to clean up before the ceremony. 

The hard work and dedication of those involved has paid off. As we look back on this image later in life, we can be reminded of the immense dedication and effort that went into this special moment. 

The incredible amount of positive comments still to this day - make it even more worth while and believe me it gives not just me justification at home but also makes my family proud thanks again 🇬🇧👍🏻

Hi everyone, I'm sitting here watching Christmas movies, I'm remembering something important: faith. Throughout my life, I've put tons of work into something I believed in – 2-stroke only racing. While we've recently incorporated 4-stroke, Pit Bikes, Balance bikes -  I want you to have faith in us. We make these decisions for strong reasons and always aim to make the right choices for the future of UK motocross.

Over the years, I've realized how much I haven't been doing this alone. I owe so much to those who have guided me and had faith in me. They've seen the best in me and I'm thankful for that ( some have past ). So this holiday season, I want to encourage you all to keep the faith as well. Whether you're trying to reach a goal or just getting through life's challenges, never give up, have faith, and believe in yourselves and those around you. 🫶🏻 #JustGotStarted

Thoughts ?
YOUTH/Clubman membership benefits.We’re excited to offer some great perks for those who join our community. First up, this membership would be a partnered with Sellindge Mx and Ringmer Mx to offer our club members discounted track fees.
But that’s not all, we also have limited midweek Surron rides, E5 and balance bike practices available exclusively for our members ( entry-level welcome ). So if you want to hit the dirt during the week, you can do it at a discounted rate. Plus, we have cheaper bike hire options available in the summer for all those who want to try out different E- bikes without breaking the bank.
We also offer a members-only ride day at the end of the year. It’s a chance for all of us to get together and have a blast on the track while enjoying some exclusive discounts and offers.
But it’s not just about the perks and discounts,our club also organizes some super fun events and activities throughout the year. From limited training days to our own club race, we plan to have something for every member to enjoy
One of the biggest advantages of our club membership is the ability to purchase an ACU license. This is a requirement for all of the above activities and events, and being a member makes it easier for you to get your license without any hassle.
You might have noticed that we’re pretty casual here. That’s because we want everyone to feel comfortable and welcome in our club. We’re all about having a good time with like-minded individuals who share the same love for motocross.
We’re a community of riders who are constantly learning and improving our skills, and we want to make sure that all our members feel supported in their journey. That’s why our club is open to riders of all ages and skill levels – from balance bikes to adults, everyone is welcome.
We understand that motocross can be an expensive sport, so we try our best to provide affordable options and discounts for our members. We want to make it accessible for everyone who has a passion for riding.
So if you’re looking to join a community of riders who share your love for motocross and want to have some serious fun on the track, then our clubman membership is perfect for you.
